[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:51:10 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: bob@builder.com Message-ID: <1578598567.3227.1673398270675@3d07dbf16876> Subject: Mrs Emis Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_3224_1955580665.1673398270672" ------=_Part_3224_1955580665.1673398270672 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_3225_1176987830.1673398270672" ------=_Part_3225_1176987830.1673398270672 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_3226_304627021.1673398270672" ------=_Part_3226_304627021.1673398270672 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Bob Builder, Mrs Emis Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Mrs Emis Patient 1 Please be my carer. ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=wtsHLJG5cS Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=wtsHLJG5cS 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Mrs Emis Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_3226_304627021.1673398270672 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Bob Builder,

Mrs Emis Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Mrs Emis Patient 1

Please be my carer.

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=wtsHLJG5cS

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=wtsHLJG5cS
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Mrs Emis Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-6/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=jVxa8BohhQ 3. What happens after I register? Mrs Emis Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Mrs Emis Patient 1

Please be my carer.

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=jVxa8BohhQ

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-6/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=jVxa8BohhQ
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Mrs Emis Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-6/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team
